  "prompt": "How do you clean a penny board?",
  "response": "Cleaning a penny board can help maintain its appearance and performance. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to clean your penny board:\n\n### Materials Needed:\n- Bucket or large container\n- Mild dish soap\n- Warm water\n- Soft brush or sponge\n- Toothbrush (for hard-to-reach areas)\n- Towel or rag\n- Drying cloth\n\n### Steps:\n\n1. **Preparation**:\n   - Remove the trucks (wheels and metal parts).\n   - This can be done using a skate tool or wrench to unscrew the nuts.\n\n2. **Wheels and Bearings**:\n   - Soak the wheels in warm, soapy water.\n   - Use a toothbrush to clean the bearings and get rid of any dirt or debris.\n   - Rinse with clean water and let them dry completely.\n\n3. **Deck Cleaning**:\n   - Fill a bucket or large container with warm water and add a small amount of mild dish soap.\n   - Dip a soft brush or sponge into the soapy water and scrub the deck.\n   - Pay extra attention to grimy areas and the foot grips.\n   - For very dirty spots, use a toothbrush to scrub those areas gently.\n   \n4. **Rinse and Dry**:\n   - Rinse the deck thoroughly with clean water to remove any soap residue.\n   - Use a towel or rag to wipe off excess water.\n   - Allow the deck to air dry completely, ideally in a well-ventilated area.\n\n5. **Reassemble**:\n   - Once all the components are dry, reattach the trucks and wheels.\n   - Ensure everything is tightly secured.\n\n### Tips:\n- Avoid using harsh chemicals or abrasive brushes as these can damage the penny board's plastic deck.\n- Regular cleaning helps prevent grime build-up and extends the lifespan of your board.\n- If the board is extremely dirty, you might need to repeat the cleaning process a few times.\n\nBy following these steps, you can keep your penny board looking good and performing well.",
